      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "I started looking into this & have a question about desired default behavior. Right now, `AvailableCoins` can be invoked without passing in a `CCoinControl` object, as done in `ListCoins` here: https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/0c9de67f343c0e740a7f488e85270d519a352119/src/wallet/wallet.cpp#L2348  The function declaration in the header handles this behavior by defaulting `CCoinControl` to a `nullptr`. Having that null pointer obviously creates an issue when trying to access `m_min_depth` on coin control. \r\n\r\nThe two options I see: \r\n1. Have `AvailableCoins` default to creating a new coin control. \r\n2. Remove the default & require the caller to create a new coin control.  \r\nThe second option seems preferable because the caller can manage memory cleanup.  There could also be other ways to handle. \r\n\r\nThoughts? ",
      "created_at" : "2019-04-16T23:06:01Z",
      "html_url" : "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/15823#issuecomment-483875676",
      "id" : 483875676,
      "issue_url" : "https://api.github.com/repos/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/15823",
      "node_id" : "MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ4Mzg3NTY3Ng==",
      "updated_at" : "2019-04-16T23:14:09Z",
